20/* The migration of target macros to target hooks works as follows:
21
22 1. Create a target hook that uses the existing target macros to
23 implement the same functionality.
24
25 2. Convert all the MI files to use the hook instead of the macro.
26
27 3. Repeat for a majority of the remaining target macros. This will
28 take some time.
29
30 4. Tell target maintainers to start migrating.
31
32 5. Eventually convert the backends to override the hook instead of
33 defining the macros. This will take some time too.
34
35 6. TBD when, poison the macros. Unmigrated targets will break at
36 this point.
37
38 Note that we expect steps 1-3 to be done by the people that
39 understand what the MI does with each macro, and step 5 to be done
40 by the target maintainers for their respective targets.
41
42 Note that steps 1 and 2 don't have to be done together, but no
43 target can override the new hook until step 2 is complete for it.
44
45 Once the macros are poisoned, we will revert to the old migration
46 rules - migrate the macro, callers, and targets all at once. This
47 comment can thus be removed at that point. */
48

108int
109default_unspec_may_trap_p (const_rtx x, unsigned flags)
110{
111 int i;
112
113 /* Any floating arithmetic may trap. */
114 if ((SCALAR_FLOAT_MODE_P (GET_MODE (x)) && flag_trapping_math))
115 return 1;
116
117 for (i = 0; i < XVECLEN (x, 0); ++i)
118 {
119 if (may_trap_p_1 (XVECEXP (x, 0, i), flags))
120 return 1;
121 }
122
123 return 0;
124}

289/* Returns the size of the cookie to use when allocating an array
290 whose elements have the indicated TYPE. Assumes that it is already
291 known that a cookie is needed. */
292
293tree
294default_cxx_get_cookie_size (tree type)
295{
296 tree cookie_size;
297
298 /* We need to allocate an additional max (sizeof (size_t), alignof
299 (true_type)) bytes. */
300 tree sizetype_size;
301 tree type_align;
302
303 sizetype_size = size_in_bytes (sizetype);
304 type_align = size_int (TYPE_ALIGN_UNIT (type));
305 if (tree_int_cst_lt (type_align, sizetype_size))
306 cookie_size = sizetype_size;
307 else
308 cookie_size = type_align;
309
310 return cookie_size;
311}

377tree
378default_mangle_assembler_name (const char *name ATTRIBUTE_UNUSED)
379{
380 const char *skipped = name + (*name == '*' ? 1 : 0);
381 const char *stripped = targetm.strip_name_encoding (skipped);

383 stripped = ACONCAT ((user_label_prefix, stripped, NULL));
384 return get_identifier (stripped);

387/* True if MODE is valid for the target. By "valid", we mean able to
388 be manipulated in non-trivial ways. In particular, this means all
389 the arithmetic is supported.
390
391 By default we guess this means that any C type is supported. If
392 we can't map the mode back to a type that would be available in C,
393 then reject it. Special case, here, is the double-word arithmetic
394 supported by optabs.c. */
395
396bool
397default_scalar_mode_supported_p (machine_mode mode)
398{
399 int precision = GET_MODE_PRECISION (mode);
400
401 switch (GET_MODE_CLASS (mode))
402 {
403 case MODE_PARTIAL_INT:
404 case MODE_INT:
405 if (precision == CHAR_TYPE_SIZE)
406 return true;
407 if (precision == SHORT_TYPE_SIZE)
408 return true;
409 if (precision == INT_TYPE_SIZE)
410 return true;
411 if (precision == LONG_TYPE_SIZE)
412 return true;
413 if (precision == LONG_LONG_TYPE_SIZE)
414 return true;
415 if (precision == 2 * BITS_PER_WORD)
416 return true;
417 return false;
418
419 case MODE_FLOAT:
420 if (precision == FLOAT_TYPE_SIZE)
421 return true;
422 if (precision == DOUBLE_TYPE_SIZE)
423 return true;
424 if (precision == LONG_DOUBLE_TYPE_SIZE)
425 return true;
426 return false;
427
428 case MODE_DECIMAL_FLOAT:
429 case MODE_FRACT:
430 case MODE_UFRACT:
431 case MODE_ACCUM:
432 case MODE_UACCUM:
433 return false;
434
435 default:
436 gcc_unreachable ();
437 }
438}

467/* Return the machine mode to use for the type _FloatN, if EXTENDED is
468 false, or _FloatNx, if EXTENDED is true, or VOIDmode if not
469 supported. */
470machine_mode
471default_floatn_mode (int n, bool extended)
472{
473 if (extended)
474 {
475 machine_mode cand1 = VOIDmode, cand2 = VOIDmode;
476 switch (n)
477 {
478 case 32:
479#ifdef HAVE_DFmode
480 cand1 = DFmode;
481#endif
482 break;
483
484 case 64:
485#ifdef HAVE_XFmode
486 cand1 = XFmode;
487#endif
488#ifdef HAVE_TFmode
489 cand2 = TFmode;
490#endif
491 break;
492
493 case 128:
494 break;
495
496 default:
497 /* Those are the only valid _FloatNx types. */
498 gcc_unreachable ();
499 }
500 if (cand1 != VOIDmode
501 && REAL_MODE_FORMAT (cand1)->ieee_bits > n
502 && targetm.scalar_mode_supported_p (cand1)
503 && targetm.libgcc_floating_mode_supported_p (cand1))
504 return cand1;
505 if (cand2 != VOIDmode
506 && REAL_MODE_FORMAT (cand2)->ieee_bits > n
507 && targetm.scalar_mode_supported_p (cand2)
508 && targetm.libgcc_floating_mode_supported_p (cand2))
509 return cand2;
510 }
511 else
512 {
513 machine_mode cand = VOIDmode;
514 switch (n)
515 {
516 case 16:
517 /* Always enable _Float16 if we have basic support for the mode.
518 Targets can control the range and precision of operations on
519 the _Float16 type using TARGET_C_EXCESS_PRECISION. */
520#ifdef HAVE_HFmode
521 cand = HFmode;
522#endif
523 break;
524
525 case 32:
526#ifdef HAVE_SFmode
527 cand = SFmode;
528#endif
529 break;
530
531 case 64:
532#ifdef HAVE_DFmode
533 cand = DFmode;
534#endif
535 break;
536
537 case 128:
538#ifdef HAVE_TFmode
539 cand = TFmode;
540#endif
541 break;
542
543 default:
544 break;
545 }
546 if (cand != VOIDmode
547 && REAL_MODE_FORMAT (cand)->ieee_bits == n
548 && targetm.scalar_mode_supported_p (cand)
549 && targetm.libgcc_floating_mode_supported_p (cand))
550 return cand;
551 }
552 return VOIDmode;
553}

605/* NULL if INSN insn is valid within a low-overhead loop, otherwise returns
606 an error message.
607
608 This function checks whether a given INSN is valid within a low-overhead
609 loop. If INSN is invalid it returns the reason for that, otherwise it
610 returns NULL. A called function may clobber any special registers required
611 for low-overhead looping. Additionally, some targets (eg, PPC) use the count
612 register for branch on table instructions. We reject the doloop pattern in
613 these cases. */
614
615const char *
616default_invalid_within_doloop (const rtx_insn *insn)
617{
618 if (CALL_P (insn))
619 return "Function call in loop.";
620
621 if (tablejump_p (insn, NULL, NULL) || computed_jump_p (insn))
622 return "Computed branch in the loop.";
623
624 return NULL;
625}

653/* Default vectorizer cost model values. */
654
655int
656default_builtin_vectorization_cost (enum vect_cost_for_stmt type_of_cost,
657 tree vectype,
658 int misalign ATTRIBUTE_UNUSED)
659{
660 switch (type_of_cost)
661 {
662 case scalar_stmt:
663 case scalar_load:
664 case scalar_store:
665 case vector_stmt:
666 case vector_load:
667 case vector_store:
668 case vec_to_scalar:
669 case scalar_to_vec:
670 case cond_branch_not_taken:
671 case vec_perm:
672 case vec_promote_demote:
673 return 1;
674
675 case unaligned_load:
676 case unaligned_store:
677 return 2;
678
679 case cond_branch_taken:
680 return 3;
681
682 case vec_construct:
683 return TYPE_VECTOR_SUBPARTS (vectype) - 1;
684
685 default:
686 gcc_unreachable ();
687 }
688}

780/* Initialize the stack protection decls. */
781
782/* Stack protection related decls living in libgcc. */
783static GTY(()) tree stack_chk_guard_decl;
784
785tree
786default_stack_protect_guard (void)
787{
788 tree t = stack_chk_guard_decl;
789
790 if (t == NULL)
791 {
792 rtx x;
793
794 t = build_decl (UNKNOWN_LOCATION,
795 VAR_DECL, get_identifier ("__stack_chk_guard"),
796 ptr_type_node);
797 TREE_STATIC (t) = 1;
798 TREE_PUBLIC (t) = 1;
799 DECL_EXTERNAL (t) = 1;
800 TREE_USED (t) = 1;
801 TREE_THIS_VOLATILE (t) = 1;
802 DECL_ARTIFICIAL (t) = 1;
803 DECL_IGNORED_P (t) = 1;
804
805 /* Do not share RTL as the declaration is visible outside of
806 current function. */
807 x = DECL_RTL (t);
808 RTX_FLAG (x, used) = 1;
809
810 stack_chk_guard_decl = t;
811 }
812
813 return t;
814}

816static GTY(()) tree stack_chk_fail_decl;
817
818tree
819default_external_stack_protect_fail (void)
820{
821 tree t = stack_chk_fail_decl;
822
823 if (t == NULL_TREE)
824 {
825 t = build_function_type_list (void_type_node, NULL_TREE);
826 t = build_decl (UNKNOWN_LOCATION,
827 FUNCTION_DECL, get_identifier ("__stack_chk_fail"), t);
828 TREE_STATIC (t) = 1;
829 TREE_PUBLIC (t) = 1;
830 DECL_EXTERNAL (t) = 1;
831 TREE_USED (t) = 1;
832 TREE_THIS_VOLATILE (t) = 1;
833 TREE_NOTHROW (t) = 1;
834 DECL_ARTIFICIAL (t) = 1;
835 DECL_IGNORED_P (t) = 1;
836 DECL_VISIBILITY (t) = VISIBILITY_DEFAULT;
837 DECL_VISIBILITY_SPECIFIED (t) = 1;

1032reg_class_t
1033default_secondary_reload (bool in_p ATTRIBUTE_UNUSED, rtx x ATTRIBUTE_UNUSED,
1034 reg_class_t reload_class_i ATTRIBUTE_UNUSED,
1035 machine_mode reload_mode ATTRIBUTE_UNUSED,
1036 secondary_reload_info *sri)
1037{
1038 enum reg_class rclass = NO_REGS;
1039 enum reg_class reload_class = (enum reg_class) reload_class_i;
1040
1041 if (sri->prev_sri && sri->prev_sri->t_icode != CODE_FOR_nothing)
1042 {
1043 sri->icode = sri->prev_sri->t_icode;
1044 return NO_REGS;
1045 }
1046#ifdef SECONDARY_INPUT_RELOAD_CLASS
1047 if (in_p)
1048 rclass = SECONDARY_INPUT_RELOAD_CLASS (reload_class, reload_mode, x);
1049#endif
1050#ifdef SECONDARY_OUTPUT_RELOAD_CLASS
1051 if (! in_p)
1052 rclass = SECONDARY_OUTPUT_RELOAD_CLASS (reload_class, reload_mode, x);
1053#endif
1054 if (rclass != NO_REGS)
1055 {
1056 enum insn_code icode
1057 = direct_optab_handler (in_p ? reload_in_optab : reload_out_optab,
1058 reload_mode);
1059
1060 if (icode != CODE_FOR_nothing
1061 && !insn_operand_matches (icode, in_p, x))
1062 icode = CODE_FOR_nothing;
1063 else if (icode != CODE_FOR_nothing)
1064 {
1065 const char *insn_constraint, *scratch_constraint;
1066 enum reg_class insn_class, scratch_class;
1067
1068 gcc_assert (insn_data[(int) icode].n_operands == 3);
1069 insn_constraint = insn_data[(int) icode].operand[!in_p].constraint;
1070 if (!*insn_constraint)
1071 insn_class = ALL_REGS;
1072 else
1073 {
1074 if (in_p)
1075 {
1076 gcc_assert (*insn_constraint == '=');
1077 insn_constraint++;
1078 }
1079 insn_class = (reg_class_for_constraint
1080 (lookup_constraint (insn_constraint)));
1081 gcc_assert (insn_class != NO_REGS);
1082 }
1083
1084 scratch_constraint = insn_data[(int) icode].operand[2].constraint;
1085 /* The scratch register's constraint must start with "=&",
1086 except for an input reload, where only "=" is necessary,
1087 and where it might be beneficial to re-use registers from
1088 the input. */
1089 gcc_assert (scratch_constraint[0] == '='
1090 && (in_p || scratch_constraint[1] == '&'));
1091 scratch_constraint++;
1092 if (*scratch_constraint == '&')
1093 scratch_constraint++;
1094 scratch_class = (reg_class_for_constraint
1095 (lookup_constraint (scratch_constraint)));
1096
1097 if (reg_class_subset_p (reload_class, insn_class))
1098 {
1099 gcc_assert (scratch_class == rclass);
1100 rclass = NO_REGS;
1101 }
1102 else
1103 rclass = insn_class;
1104
1105 }
1106 if (rclass == NO_REGS)
1107 sri->icode = icode;
1108 else
1109 sri->t_icode = icode;
1110 }
1111 return rclass;
1112}

1203/* By default, the cost model accumulates three separate costs (prologue,
1204 loop body, and epilogue) for a vectorized loop or block. So allocate an
1205 array of three unsigned ints, set it to zero, and return its address. */
1206
1207void *
1208default_init_cost (struct loop *loop_info ATTRIBUTE_UNUSED)
1209{
1210 unsigned *cost = XNEWVEC (unsigned, 3);
1211 cost[vect_prologue] = cost[vect_body] = cost[vect_epilogue] = 0;
1212 return cost;
1213}
1214
1215/* By default, the cost model looks up the cost of the given statement
1216 kind and mode, multiplies it by the occurrence count, accumulates
1217 it into the cost specified by WHERE, and returns the cost added. */
1218
1219unsigned
1220default_add_stmt_cost (void *data, int count, enum vect_cost_for_stmt kind,
1221 struct _stmt_vec_info *stmt_info, int misalign,
1222 enum vect_cost_model_location where)
1223{
1224 unsigned *cost = (unsigned *) data;
1225 unsigned retval = 0;
1226
1227 tree vectype = stmt_info ? stmt_vectype (stmt_info) : NULL_TREE;
1228 int stmt_cost = targetm.vectorize.builtin_vectorization_cost (kind, vectype,
1229 misalign);
1230 /* Statements in an inner loop relative to the loop being
1231 vectorized are weighted more heavily. The value here is
1232 arbitrary and could potentially be improved with analysis. */
1233 if (where == vect_body && stmt_info && stmt_in_inner_loop_p (stmt_info))
1234 count *= 50; /* FIXME. */
1235
1236 retval = (unsigned) (count * stmt_cost);
1237 cost[where] += retval;
1238
1239 return retval;
1240}

1247{
1248 unsigned *cost = (unsigned *) data;
1249 *prologue_cost = cost[vect_prologue];
1250 *body_cost = cost[vect_body];
1251 *epilogue_cost = cost[vect_epilogue];

1270/* Determine whether the memory reference specified by REF may alias
1271 the C libraries errno location. */
1272bool
1273default_ref_may_alias_errno (ao_ref *ref)
1274{
1275 tree base = ao_ref_base (ref);
1276 /* The default implementation assumes the errno location is
1277 a declaration of type int or is always accessed via a
1278 pointer to int. We assume that accesses to errno are
1279 not deliberately obfuscated (even in conforming ways). */
1280 if (TYPE_UNSIGNED (TREE_TYPE (base))
1281 || TYPE_MODE (TREE_TYPE (base)) != TYPE_MODE (integer_type_node))
1282 return false;
1283 /* The default implementation assumes an errno location
1284 declaration is never defined in the current compilation unit. */
1285 if (DECL_P (base)
1286 && !TREE_STATIC (base))
1287 return true;
1288 else if (TREE_CODE (base) == MEM_REF
1289 && TREE_CODE (TREE_OPERAND (base, 0)) == SSA_NAME)
1290 {
1291 struct ptr_info_def *pi = SSA_NAME_PTR_INFO (TREE_OPERAND (base, 0));
1292 return !pi || pi->pt.anything || pi->pt.nonlocal;
1293 }
1294 return false;
1295}

1450bool
1451default_target_can_inline_p (tree caller, tree callee)
1452{
1453 bool ret = false;
1454 tree callee_opts = DECL_FUNCTION_SPECIFIC_TARGET (callee);
1455 tree caller_opts = DECL_FUNCTION_SPECIFIC_TARGET (caller);
1456
1457 /* If callee has no option attributes, then it is ok to inline */
1458 if (!callee_opts)
1459 ret = true;
1460
1461 /* If caller has no option attributes, but callee does then it is not ok to
1462 inline */
1463 else if (!caller_opts)
1464 ret = false;
1465
1466 /* If both caller and callee have attributes, assume that if the
1467 pointer is different, the two functions have different target
1468 options since build_target_option_node uses a hash table for the
1469 options. */
1470 else
1471 ret = (callee_opts == caller_opts);
1472
1473 return ret;
1474}

1552/* For hooks which use the MOVE_RATIO macro, this gives the legacy default
1553 behavior. SPEED_P is true if we are compiling for speed. */

1557{

1559#ifdef MOVE_RATIO
1560 move_ratio = (unsigned int) MOVE_RATIO (speed_p);
1561#else
1562#if defined (HAVE_movmemqi) || defined (HAVE_movmemhi) || defined (HAVE_movmemsi) || defined (HAVE_movmemdi) || defined (HAVE_movmemti)
1563 move_ratio = 2;
1564#else /* No movmem patterns, pick a default. */
1565 move_ratio = ((speed_p) ? 15 : 3);
1566#endif
1567#endif
1568 return move_ratio;
1569}

1571/* Return TRUE if the move_by_pieces/set_by_pieces infrastructure should be
1572 used; return FALSE if the movmem/setmem optab should be expanded, or
1573 a call to memcpy emitted. */
1574
1575bool
1576default_use_by_pieces_infrastructure_p (unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT size,
1577 unsigned int alignment,
1578 enum by_pieces_operation op,
1579 bool speed_p)
1580{
1581 unsigned int max_size = 0;
1582 unsigned int ratio = 0;
1583
1584 switch (op)
1585 {
1586 case CLEAR_BY_PIECES:
1587 max_size = STORE_MAX_PIECES;
1588 ratio = CLEAR_RATIO (speed_p);
1589 break;
1590 case MOVE_BY_PIECES:
1591 max_size = MOVE_MAX_PIECES;
1592 ratio = get_move_ratio (speed_p);
1593 break;
1594 case SET_BY_PIECES:
1595 max_size = STORE_MAX_PIECES;
1596 ratio = SET_RATIO (speed_p);
1597 break;
1598 case STORE_BY_PIECES:
1599 max_size = STORE_MAX_PIECES;
1600 ratio = get_move_ratio (speed_p);
1601 break;
1602 case COMPARE_BY_PIECES:
1603 max_size = COMPARE_MAX_PIECES;
1604 /* Pick a likely default, just as in get_move_ratio. */
1605 ratio = speed_p ? 15 : 3;
1606 break;
1607 }
1608
1609 return by_pieces_ninsns (size, alignment, max_size + 1, op) < ratio;
1610}

1734/* Return true if the state of option OPTION should be stored in PCH files
1735 and checked by default_pch_valid_p. Store the option's current state
1736 in STATE if so. */
1737
1738static inline bool
1739option_affects_pch_p (int option, struct cl_option_state *state)
1740{
1741 if ((cl_options[option].flags & CL_TARGET) == 0)
1742 return false;
1743 if ((cl_options[option].flags & CL_PCH_IGNORE) != 0)
1744 return false;
1745 if (option_flag_var (option, &global_options) == &target_flags)
1746 if (targetm.check_pch_target_flags)
1747 return false;
1748 return get_option_state (&global_options, option, state);
1749}

1751/* Default version of get_pch_validity.
1752 By default, every flag difference is fatal; that will be mostly right for
1753 most targets, but completely right for very few. */
1754
1755void *
1756default_get_pch_validity (size_t *sz)
1757{
1758 struct cl_option_state state;
1759 size_t i;
1760 char *result, *r;
1761
1762 *sz = 2;
1763 if (targetm.check_pch_target_flags)
1764 *sz += sizeof (target_flags);
1765 for (i = 0; i < cl_options_count; i++)
1766 if (option_affects_pch_p (i, &state))
1767 *sz += state.size;
1768
1769 result = r = XNEWVEC (char, *sz);
1770 r[0] = flag_pic;
1771 r[1] = flag_pie;
1772 r += 2;
1773 if (targetm.check_pch_target_flags)
1774 {
1775 memcpy (r, &target_flags, sizeof (target_flags));
1776 r += sizeof (target_flags);
1777 }
1778
1779 for (i = 0; i < cl_options_count; i++)
1780 if (option_affects_pch_p (i, &state))
1781 {
1782 memcpy (r, state.data, state.size);
1783 r += state.size;
1784 }
1785
1786 return result;
1787}

1799/* Default version of pch_valid_p. */
1800
1801const char *
1802default_pch_valid_p (const void *data_p, size_t len)
1803{
1804 struct cl_option_state state;
1805 const char *data = (const char *)data_p;
1806 size_t i;
1807
1808 /* -fpic and -fpie also usually make a PCH invalid. */
1809 if (data[0] != flag_pic)
1810 return _("created and used with different settings of -fpic");
1811 if (data[1] != flag_pie)
1812 return _("created and used with different settings of -fpie");
1813 data += 2;
1814
1815 /* Check target_flags. */
1816 if (targetm.check_pch_target_flags)
1817 {
1818 int tf;
1819 const char *r;
1820
1821 memcpy (&tf, data, sizeof (target_flags));
1822 data += sizeof (target_flags);
1823 len -= sizeof (target_flags);
1824 r = targetm.check_pch_target_flags (tf);
1825 if (r != NULL)
1826 return r;
1827 }
1828
1829 for (i = 0; i < cl_options_count; i++)
1830 if (option_affects_pch_p (i, &state))
1831 {
1832 if (memcmp (data, state.data, state.size) != 0)
1833 return pch_option_mismatch (cl_options[i].opt_text);
1834 data += state.size;
1835 len -= state.size;
1836 }
1837
1838 return NULL;
1839}

1914/* The "standard" implementation of va_arg: read the value from the
1915 current (padded) address and increment by the (padded) size. */
1916
1917tree
1918std_gimplify_va_arg_expr (tree valist, tree type, gimple_seq *pre_p,
1919 gimple_seq *post_p)
1920{
1921 tree addr, t, type_size, rounded_size, valist_tmp;
1922 unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT align, boundary;
1923 bool indirect;
1924
1925 /* All of the alignment and movement below is for args-grow-up machines.
1926 As of 2004, there are only 3 ARGS_GROW_DOWNWARD targets, and they all
1927 implement their own specialized gimplify_va_arg_expr routines. */
1928 if (ARGS_GROW_DOWNWARD)
1929 gcc_unreachable ();
1930
1931 indirect = pass_by_reference (NULL, TYPE_MODE (type), type, false);
1932 if (indirect)
1933 type = build_pointer_type (type);
1934
1935 align = PARM_BOUNDARY / BITS_PER_UNIT;
1936 boundary = targetm.calls.function_arg_boundary (TYPE_MODE (type), type);
1937
1938 /* When we align parameter on stack for caller, if the parameter
1939 alignment is beyond MAX_SUPPORTED_STACK_ALIGNMENT, it will be
1940 aligned at MAX_SUPPORTED_STACK_ALIGNMENT. We will match callee
1941 here with caller. */
1942 if (boundary > MAX_SUPPORTED_STACK_ALIGNMENT)
1943 boundary = MAX_SUPPORTED_STACK_ALIGNMENT;
1944
1945 boundary /= BITS_PER_UNIT;
1946
1947 /* Hoist the valist value into a temporary for the moment. */
1948 valist_tmp = get_initialized_tmp_var (valist, pre_p, NULL);
1949
1950 /* va_list pointer is aligned to PARM_BOUNDARY. If argument actually
1951 requires greater alignment, we must perform dynamic alignment. */
1952 if (boundary > align
1953 && !integer_zerop (TYPE_SIZE (type)))
1954 {
1955 t = build2 (MODIFY_EXPR, TREE_TYPE (valist), valist_tmp,
1956 fold_build_pointer_plus_hwi (valist_tmp, boundary - 1));
1957 gimplify_and_add (t, pre_p);
1958
1959 t = build2 (MODIFY_EXPR, TREE_TYPE (valist), valist_tmp,
1960 fold_build2 (BIT_AND_EXPR, TREE_TYPE (valist),
1961 valist_tmp,
1962 build_int_cst (TREE_TYPE (valist), -boundary)));
1963 gimplify_and_add (t, pre_p);
1964 }
1965 else
1966 boundary = align;
1967
1968 /* If the actual alignment is less than the alignment of the type,
1969 adjust the type accordingly so that we don't assume strict alignment
1970 when dereferencing the pointer. */
1971 boundary *= BITS_PER_UNIT;
1972 if (boundary < TYPE_ALIGN (type))
1973 {
1974 type = build_variant_type_copy (type);
1975 SET_TYPE_ALIGN (type, boundary);
1976 }
1977
1978 /* Compute the rounded size of the type. */
1979 type_size = size_in_bytes (type);
1980 rounded_size = round_up (type_size, align);
1981
1982 /* Reduce rounded_size so it's sharable with the postqueue. */
1983 gimplify_expr (&rounded_size, pre_p, post_p, is_gimple_val, fb_rvalue);
1984
1985 /* Get AP. */
1986 addr = valist_tmp;
1987 if (PAD_VARARGS_DOWN && !integer_zerop (rounded_size))
1988 {
1989 /* Small args are padded downward. */
1990 t = fold_build2_loc (input_location, GT_EXPR, sizetype,
1991 rounded_size, size_int (align));
1992 t = fold_build3 (COND_EXPR, sizetype, t, size_zero_node,
1993 size_binop (MINUS_EXPR, rounded_size, type_size));
1994 addr = fold_build_pointer_plus (addr, t);
1995 }
1996
1997 /* Compute new value for AP. */
1998 t = fold_build_pointer_plus (valist_tmp, rounded_size);
1999 t = build2 (MODIFY_EXPR, TREE_TYPE (valist), valist, t);
2000 gimplify_and_add (t, pre_p);
2001
2002 addr = fold_convert (build_pointer_type (type), addr);
2003
2004 if (indirect)
2005 addr = build_va_arg_indirect_ref (addr);
2006
2007 return build_va_arg_indirect_ref (addr);
2008}
